==Etymology==
From Greek '''monachos''', ''single'' or ''[[alone]]''

==Latin==
===Noun===
'''monachus''' ''m'', genitive '''[[monachi]]'''

Second declension

# [[monk]]; (male) member of a religious community which lives isolated or apart from the rest of the world, such as the [[Benedictines]] or [[Buddhists]].  The feminine form is ''[[monacha]]''.

